      • updateView

        public void updateView(DataEvent cause)
        Description copied from class: CalcValue
        Update the CalcValue.cache value. The default implementation calls CalcValue.calc(). Sub-classes may override this to provide a more efficient implementation, for example avoiding autoboxing if a primitive type is stored.

      • calc

        public Float calc()
        Description copied from class: CalcValue
        This is the method where you implement the function. Implementations must calculate and return the value that a call to DataValue.get() should return (based on the AbstractValueView.inputValues if applicable). The value returned will be cached and returned by calls to CalcValue.get().
        Specified by:
        calc in class CalcValue<I,Float>

      • calcFloat

        public float calcFloat()
        Description copied from class: CalcValue
        Primitive equivalent to CalcValue.calc(). This allows for more efficient implementations of #updateView(Object) if a primitive type is stored. This implementation throws an UnsupportedOperationException.

        calcFloat in class CalcValue<I,Float>
